	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm sure this game violates more than the 8 sprite per scanline limit. It probably also violates the 256 sprites limit as well as the 256 tile selection limit. Most likely it also violates the palette limit. It's not hard to fool people who don't know about the NES's limits. Just like the average listener doesn't really pay attention to the fact that most artists today are completely pitch corrected in singing, the average player won't understand that this game violates several laws of the NES.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


